benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogs - Retrieve audit logs by account id

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval for existing accounts (TC01) and account exists but has no logs (TC02).
Not Found/Error Handling: Account does not exist (TC03) and invalid accountId format (TC04) tested.
Authorization: Tests for missing (TC05) and invalid token (TC06) scenarios present.
Query Parameters: Extra query parameters ignored (TC07) covered.
Server/Error Handling: System/database unavailable leading to 500 (TC08) covered.
Large Datasets/Performance: Large number of logs (TC09) and concurrency (TC14) addressed.
Edge/Negative Scenarios: Injection attempt (TC10) and timeout under load (TC11) included.
Regression/Backward Compatibility: Regression (TC12) and backward compatibility with older client (TC13) accounted.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination mechanics (page size, page number, next/prev links) though TC09 implies large data; no dedicated pagination validation is present.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related cache invalidation.
Rate Limiting: No explicit tests for rate limiting/throttling beyond concurrency (TC14).
Authorization Nuance: Only 401 tested; no scenario differentiating 403 (forbidden) vs 401 (unauthorized) in detail.
Edge Case Robustness: No test for malformed nested paths or path parameter encoding beyond accountId format (e.g., special characters handling beyond injection test).
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination scenarios to verify page size handling, paging parameters, and correct total counts when listing audit logs (especially for TC09-like large datasets).
Add caching header validations: verify ETag/Cache-Control presence and correct behavior on subsequent identical requests.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to confirm graceful degradation under burst traffic.
Differentiate authorization failure modes: include a 403 scenario when user is authenticated but lacks permission, in addition to 401 scenarios.
Expand input validation coverage for path parameters: include tests for edge-encoded characters and additional length constraints to prevent edge-case injections.
Consider adding explicit schema validation tests to ensure AuditLog objects contain required fields with correct data types across responses.
